<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="251" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-16"><hi rend="italic">February 16,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay acknowledges Mr. Powell’s telegram of the 9th instant, and
                            states that under custom prevailing in the Dominican Republic, military
                            authorities are not justified in invading consular offices and capturing
                            refugees. Instructs him to make proper representations.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>